ZH: 我们决不能亏待那些为公司付出努力的员工。
EN: We must never mistreat the employees who work hard for the company.

ZH: 家人是我们一生中最不能亏待的人。
EN: Family is the people we must never mistreat in our whole life.

ZH: 我感到很愧疚，我亏待了我最好的朋友。
EN: I feel guilty because I mistreated my best friend.

ZH: 这家餐厅经常亏待他们的客户。
EN: This restaurant often mistreats their customers.

ZH: 我还没弄明白为什么他们会亏待我。
EN: I haven't figured out why they mistreated me.

ZH: 亲人之间不应该亏待彼此。
EN: Family should not mistreat each other.

ZH: 他忍受了多年的亏待，终于辞职了。
EN: After enduring years of mistreatment, he finally resigned.

ZH: 这个公司以亏待实习生而闻名。
EN: This company is notorious for mistreating interns.

ZH: 我不明白为什么他会亏待自己最的好朋友。
EN: I don't understand why he would mistreat his best friend.

ZH: 这个国家对待少数民族亏待太严重了。
EN: This country mistreats minority groups too severely.

ZH: 我发誓从今以后再也不亏待她了。
EN: I swear to never mistreat her again from now on.

ZH: 你不应该亏待那些帮助过你的人。
EN: You should not mistreat the people who have helped you.

ZH: 他因为亏待员工而受到了法律的制裁。
EN: He was legally penalized for mistreating the employees.

ZH: 无论发生什么，我都不会亏待你的。
EN: I will never mistreat you no matter what happens.

ZH: 学校应该惩罚那些亏待同学的人。
EN: Schools should punish those who mistreat their classmates.

ZH: 亏待动物是不道德的行为。
EN: Mistreating animals is an immoral act.

ZH: 他被控告亏待自己的孩子。
EN: He was accused of mistreating his own children.

ZH: 因为曾亏待我，我再也不会相信他了。
EN: I will never trust him again because he once mistreated me.

ZH: 他们亏待员工就是因为他们想要削减成本。
EN: They mistreat their employees because they want to cut costs.

ZH: 不要亏待一个对你这么好的人。
EN: Don't mistreat someone who is so good to you.
